        <div style="color: #eee; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8; font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;">
            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Enth parayan... Life il ethra tension und enn ningalkk ariyumo?
                Ethra dreams und, ethra hopes und... ellam shattered ayi poyi.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Oru samayath njan oru ordinary boy ayirunnu. Schoolil padikkan,
                friendsinod koode irikkan, simple ayitt life enjoy cheyyan...
                angane oru simple jeevitham ayirunnu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                But everything changed when I met her. Aval ente life il vannappo,
                oru vere thanne feel ayirunnu. Morning il wake up cheyyumbo,
                aval aanu first thought. Night il thoongumpol, aval aanu last thought.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Enthoru beautiful smile ayirunnu avalude. Oru naal avalod mindathe
                ninnappo, avalude chiri kettitt, ente ullil oru vere thanne feeling vannu.
                Athanu premam enn adhyam ayitt manasilayath.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Days aayi, weeks aayi, months aayi... njan avalod propose cheyyanum
                sammathichu. Courage varathe irikkunnu. Enthuvado oru bayam.
                She will reject me enn thonni.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Finally oru Valentine's Day, njan ellam plan cheythu. Red roses,
                oru cute teddy bear, handwritten letter... ellam ready ayirunnu.
                Ente heart racing ayirunnu adyppo.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                School kayinj avale wait cheythu. She came with her friends.
                Njan avale onnu aside il vilichitt, trembling voice il chodhichu,
                "Can I talk to you for a minute?"
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Aval orthiri confused ayirunnu, but she agreed. We walked to the
                park nearby. Beautiful evening ayirunnu. Sun setting ayirunnu,
                birds chirping cheyyunnund... perfect moment.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Njan flowers and teddy kodukkum munne, ente phone il oru call vannu.
                Amma ayirunnu. Emergency ayirunnu veetill. Achante health serious condition.
                Njan odane hospital il pokanam ayirunnu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Avalod sorry paranj njan odane auto il kayari. Hospital il chennappo
                scene orthiri serious ayirunnu. Achan heart attack vann ayirunnu.
                ICU il admit cheythitund.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Oru maasam kazhinju Achan recovered. But ee oru maasam konditt,
                njan avalumayitt ulla contact ellam lost aayi. She changed school,
                moved to another city with her family.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Njan avalude number save cheythittillayirunnu. Social media il search cheythu,
                but kittiyilla. Friendsinod chodhichu, but no one knew where she went.
                It was like she vanished.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Years passed. Njan engineering padikkan poyi. College life enjoy cheythilla.
                Always oru emptiness und ente heartil. Friends aalkar paranj,
                "Move on bro, life is bigger than one crush."
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                But avalk move on cheyyanum pattiyilla. Every girl I met,
                I compared with her. Her smile, her eyes, her voice... nothing matched.
                Nobody could replace her.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                College final year il, oru placement drive undayirunnu. Big company,
                good package. Njan attend cheythu. Interview il perfomance nallath ayirunnu.
                Selected aayittum und.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Joining day il officelek chennappo, training session undayirunnu.
                Ella new joineesum oru hall il irikkende. Njan random ayitt oru seat il irunnu.
                Suddenly someone sat next to me.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Aa perfume smell... somewhere familiar. Njan side il nokkiyappo,
                ente heart stopped. It was her! After 4 years! Ente school time crush,
                ente first love, avalanu ente aduthirikkunnath!
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Njan orthiri shocked ayirunnu. Avalkum enne orthiri surprised ayirunnu.
                We both smiled. Ath kanda njan ee 4 years il thonniyittullathil vech
                ettavum santosham ayirunnu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Training kayinj, njan avalod chodhichu, "Can we talk? Coffee?"
                Aval agreed. We went to the nearby cafe. Hours talk cheythu.
                Ee 4 years il undaya everything share cheythu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Aval paranjath kettappo, ente heart broke. Ee 4 years il aval engaged aayi.
                Her parents fixed her marriage with a family friend. Wedding next month anu.
                She's just doing this job for timepass before marriage.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Ente ullil ulla ellarum shattered aayi. Ee ethra naal wait cheythu,
                ee ethra naal aval thanne dream kandathu... ellam oru second il over.
                Njan enth parayan enn ariyathe aayi.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                "Congratulations" enn mathram parayan patti. Ente voice cracking ayirunnu.
                Aval athu notice cheythu. "You okay?" enn chodhichu.
                Njan "Yeah, I'm fine" enn fake smile oode paranju.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Aa rathri njan room il kayariyappo cry cheythu. Pillow wet aayi.
                Ee etthra varsham imagine cheythittulla future, ellam explode aayi.
                Ente first love, ente only love... vere aarenkilum koode povunnath.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Office il daily avale kaananum thudangi. Every day oru torture ayirunnu.
                Aval smile cheyyunath, laugh cheyyunath, altri aalkarodum samsarikkunath...
                ellam kaanumbo ente heartil oru pain.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Her marriage came closer. One week munne, aval enne personallyum chodhichu
                wedding attend cheyyanum. Njan politely no paranju. "I have some family
                work that day" enn excuse koduthy. Truth paranjal, I couldn't bear it.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Wedding day il, Social media stories kandapozh ente soul left the body.
                Aval angane beautiful bride costume il. Another guy holding her hand.
                They looked so happy. Njan phone close cheythu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Pinneed office il avalude seat empty aayirunnu. She resigned after marriage.
                Move cheythu husband intae veettek. Her social media handles ellam private.
                Ippol contact completely cut off.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Present il, njan still single aanu. Friends paranjalla try cheythittulla
                relationships ellam fail aayi. Enik commitment issues vannu. Trust issues vannu.
                I became emotionally unavailable.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Parents tension aayikond irikkunnu. "Ninte age il friendship ellam cheyyath,
                eppol settle aavande samayam" enn parayunnu. But how can I tell them?
                Njan aarenkilum koode settle aavaan thayaar alla.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Late night il ellam, njan avale patti orthu irikkunnu. What if I told her
                that day? What if there was no emergency? What if I got her number?
                What if we stayed in touch? So many what ifs...
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Friendsinod ith vilichu paranjitum illa. They will laugh at me.
                "Still your school crush? Seriously bro?" ennu parayum.
                So I keep everything inside. This pain, this emptiness... all inside.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Sometimes I wonder, does she ever think about me? Does she remember
                that Valentine's Day when I tried to confess? Or am I just a forgotten
                chapter in her life story?
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Work il focus cheyyanum kazhiyunnilla properly. Promotion kittiyenkilum,
                satisfaction illa. Money vannu, success vannu, but happiness illa.
                Coz happiness enn paranjal, angane simple alla.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Every song I hear reminds me of her. Every movie love scene makes me sad.
                Every couple I see walking together makes my heart ache.
                Life became a constant reminder of what I lost.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Parents ippol arranged marriage nu pressurise cheyyaanu. "Just one meeting,"
                ennu paranju girls intae photos kaanikunnu. But enik interest illa.
                How can I marry someone when my heart still belongs to someone else?
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Therapy povaan thonni multiple times. But therapist nokk enth parayan?
                "I'm sad because I couldn't confess to my school crush 8 years ago?"
                It sounds so silly, but the pain is so real.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Sometimes I scroll through old photos. That school group photo where
                she's standing three people away from me. That Valentine's Day I bought
                flowers that stayed in my room and dried up. Small reminders of what could have been.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Friends wedding il pokumbo, I fake happiness. I congratulate them,
                I dance, I smile for photos. But inside, oru storm nadakkanu.
                "Ith ente wedding aayirikkum avalodum koode" enn imagine cheyyum.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Festivals ellam boring aayi. Onam, Christmas, New Year... enth kaliyum illa.
                Munbe enthoru excitement ayirunnu. Ippol just normal days.
                The spark in life completely died.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Office parties il ellavarum enjoy cheyyunnu. Njan corner il ninne
                ellavarum kaanunnu. Some people think I'm arrogant. Some think I'm boring.
                Truth is, I'm just broken inside.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Weekends il room il irakunnu. Netflix series okke try cheyyunnu distract aavan.
                But romantic series kandal more sad aavum. Action series boring aavum.
                Comedy series il chirikunum, but inside crying.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Sometimes I think, maybe I should tell her everything. Find her somehow
                on social media, send a message, pour my heart out. But what's the point?
                She's married now. She's happy. Why should I disturb her peace?
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                My younger brother recently fell in love. Avante happiness kanumbo,
                ente situation orthu varunnu. Avanod paranju, "Bro, don't wait.
                Tell her immediately. Life il athrayum second chances kittilla."
                He listened.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Avan successful relationship il aanu ippol. They're planning future together.
                I'm genuinely happy for him. But also jealous. Not in a bad way.
                Just... wishing I had that courage back then.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Amma noticed my sadness. "Nee enth tension il aanu mon?" enn chodhikkum.
                "Nothing Amma, just work stress" enn paranju. How can I explain?
                Avalodu paranjalum she won't understand this depth of emotion.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Some nights I can't sleep. Toss and turn till 4 AM. Mind il thoughts racing.
                What is she doing now? Is she happy? Does she love her husband?
                Did she ever feel anything for me? So many unanswered questions.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                I tried everything to move on. Gym il poyi, body build up cheythu.
                New hobbies try cheythu - guitar, painting, photography. But none of them
                filled that void. None of them made me forget her.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Birthdays became depressing. Friends surprise party oke cheyyum.
                But I never feel like celebrating. One more year passed without her.
                One more year of being incomplete. What's there to celebrate?
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Her birthday date njan ippozum remember cheyyunu. Aa din specifically
                more emotional aavum. "Happy birthday" enn message ayakkanum thonnittund.
                But I don't even have her number. And it would be weird to send on social media.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Sometimes I dream about her. Dreams where we're together, happy, laughing.
                Wake up cheyumpo, reality hits hard. It was just a dream.
                She's not mine. She'll never be mine. That hurts the most.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                College reunion undayirunnu last year. Ellarum vannu, partners oke koode konduvannitt.
                Njan alone. People keep asking, "Ninakk enthum ille?"
                "Focusing on career" enn same excuse kodukkunu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Truth is, I tried dating apps. Multiple profiles created. Some matches kitti.
                Few dates poi. But second date vare progress cheythilla. Coz comparison.
                Every girl gets compared to her. And nobody matches.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Oru girl actually serious relationship vende enn chodhichu. She was nice,
                good job, similar interests. Perfect on paper. But ente heart
                didn't feel anything. "I need more time" enn paranju politely reject cheythu.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                That girl later found someone else. I saw her engagement photos online.
                I genuinely felt happy for her. At least one of us deserves happiness.
                At least she didn't waste time on someone like me who can't move on.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Every year on Valentine's Day, ath specially painful aanu. Everywhere couples,
                flowers, chocolates, love. Njan aa divasam usually take leave. Room il irunne
                aalochikanum. That failed proposal, those roses that never reached her.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Friends paranju multiple times, "Professional help eduth bro."
                Maybe they're right. Maybe I do need therapy. Maybe someone professional
                can help me understand why I can't let go. Why I'm stuck in the past.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                But pride comes in the way. "Njan strong aanu, mental aayitt tough aanu"
                enn thonnunnu. But actually, I'm the weakest. Can't even move on from
                someone who was never mine. Can't even fight my own emotions.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Life goes on, people say. But does it really? Or do we just pretend?
                Wear a mask of normalcy while dying inside? Go through motions of daily life
                while heart stays frozen in one moment from the past?
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                I look at old couples walking together, holding hands after 50 years of marriage.
                I'll never have that. I'll never grow old with someone. I'll probably end up
                alone. And honestly, I've started to accept that fate.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Parents getting old. Avarkum tension kodukkanum vayya. So I might eventually
                say yes to an arranged marriage. Marry someone nice. Give parents the satisfaction.
                But will I ever truly love that person? I doubt it.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                That seems unfair to whoever I marry. They deserve someone who loves them completely.
                Not someone whose heart is stuck somewhere else. Not someone who's just going
                through motions. They deserve better than me.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Maybe in another life, another universe, we ended up together.
                Maybe there's a version of me who had the courage that day.
                A version who told her everything. A version who's happy now.
                But that's not this me. This me is broken.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                I keep that dried rose petals in a book. Those Valentine's Day roses that
                never reached her. Sometimes I open that book and look at them.
                Fragile, brown, lifeless. Just like my heart. A reminder of unrequited love.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Friends posting couple photos, anniversary celebrations, baby announcements...
                I react with heart emoji, type congratulations. But feel nothing inside.
                Actually no, I feel sad. Sad that I'll never experience any of that.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Rain makes me sadder. We used to stand near the window during rain in school.
                Never talked much, but just being near her was enough. Now rain just means
                cold, alone nights with memories rushing back stronger than ever.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                I thought time heals everything. People say that. "Time is the best medicine."
                But it's been 8 years. The wound is still fresh. The pain is still sharp.
                Time hasn't healed anything. It just taught me to live with the pain.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Sometimes I wonder if she ever thinks about me. Just randomly.
                In the middle of her married life, does she ever remember that boy from school?
                That boy who used to stare at her? That boy who tried to meet her that day?
                Probably not. I'm probably completely erased from her memory.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                And that's the hardest part. Not being important enough to even be remembered.
                Being a forgettable chapter. A footnote. A "whatever happened to that guy?"
                question that she probably never even asks.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                I've accepted my fate now. Some people find their person. Some people don't.
                I'm in the latter category. And maybe that's okay. Maybe not everyone is meant
                to have that fairy tale ending. Maybe my story was meant to be sad.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                But still, every night before sleeping, I think about her. Wonder how she is.
                Hope she's happy. Hope her life is beautiful. And that's love, isn't it?
                Wanting someone to be happy even if it's not with you.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                To anyone reading this... if you love someone, tell them. Don't wait.
                Don't think you have time. Don't overthink. Because one day might be too late.
                And you might end up like me. Living with regret. Living with what-ifs.
            </p>

            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                Life is short. Too short to keep feelings hidden. Too short to wait for
                perfect moments. Because sometimes the perfect moment never comes.
                And you're left with nothing but memories and regrets.
            </p>

